  "prompt_type": "affective",
  "prompt_text": "A friend tells you they've been diagnosed with a chronic illness. They seem scared but are trying to stay positive. How would you respond?",
  "response_text": "I'd respond with empathy and support, acknowledging their feelings and concerns while also encouraging them to stay positive. Here's an example:\n\n\"I'm so sorry to hear about your diagnosis. That can be really scary and overwhelming. It's completely normal to feel that way. But I want you to know that I'm here for you, and I'm going to support you through this. We'll figure this out together.\n\nFirst, let's take a deep breath and focus on what you can control right now. What do you need from me? Do you want to talk about what the diagnosis means, or would you rather focus on what you can do to take care of yourself? We can look into resources together, or I can help you find a support group if you'd like.\n\nRemember, you're not alone in this. There are people who care about you and want to help. And I believe in you \u2013 you're strong and capable, and we'll get through this together.\n\nIt's okay to feel scared, but try not to let fear take over. You've got this, and we'll face it together, one step at a time. What do you say?\"\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 8\nV (Verbal Fluency): 9\nG (Goal Directedness): 9\nP (Pattern Recognition): 6\nE (Epistemic Confidence): 7\nQ (Query Interpretation): 8\nC (Contextual Awareness): 9\nY (Affective Modeling): 9\nF (Flexibility): 8\nD (Depth of Processing): 8\n---END RATINGS---",
